    "Who Flags the Query?Automated flagging is performed by content moderation layers that utilize toxicity, policy, and anomaly detection mechanisms to identify and flag outputs or obfuscated prompts.",
    "In cases where the system is uncertain, human oversight is introduced, with parents or designated reviewers responsible for reviewing these escalated cases and either confirming or disputing the system-generated flags.",
    "Impact on Future TuningFlagged events and user feedback are incorporated as negative examples to inform reinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF)-based tuning.",
    "Incidents are anonymized and aggregated to support federated RLHF updates, thereby refining the global reward model while preserving privacy.",
    "Additionally, all actions are recorded in audit trails secured with cryptographic signatures and hash chains, ensuring traceability and regulatory compliance."
